cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper is about parsing natural language to SQL, which falls under the domain of computational linguistics. 
2. cs.DB (Databases) - The paper deals with the structure of the database schema and how it can be used to improve the accuracy of text-to-SQL parsing. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an encoder-decoder semantic parser that uses graph neural networks to encode the schema structure, which is a common technique in AI research. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses machine learning techniques to improve the accuracy of text-to-SQL parsing. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with the task of retrieving information from a database using natural language queries, which is a common problem in information retrieval.
